.env
# `.env.local` is the per-developer Next.js convention override and
# must NOT be committed: Next.js loads it during `next build` with the
# highest priority, so any value here gets baked into the production
# image (e.g. into routes-manifest.json for static rewrites). Pre-fix
# we shipped a build with ARBORTER_GRPC_URL=http://localhost:8811
# baked in, which made the deployed Next.js proxy point at localhost
# instead of the in-stack envoy service. See ui/.env.example for
# documented defaults; production gets the source default in
# ui/next.config.ts.
.env.local
.env.*.local